yaml.kubernetes:
apiVersion: v1
kind: Namespace
metadata:
  name: opsramp-agent
---
kind: ClusterRole
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
metadata:
  name: opsrampagentcr
rules:
  - nonResourceURLs:
      - "/version"
      - "/healthz"
      - "/metrics"
    verbs: ["get"]
  - apiGroups: [""]
    resources:
      - "nodes"
      - "daemonsets"
      - "deployments"
      - "services"
      - "events"
      - "configmaps"
      - "pods"
    verbs: ["get", "list", "watch"]
  - apiGroups: [""]
    resources:
      - "pods"
      - "pods/exec"
    verbs: ["get", "list", "create"]
  - apiGroups: [""] # For Schdeuler, controller and Api Metrics collection
    resources:
      - "pods/proxy"
      - "nodes/proxy"
      - "pods/metrics"
      - "nodes/metrics"
    verbs: ["get"]
---
kind: ClusterRole
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
metadata:
  name: agent-updater
rules:
  - apiGroups: ["*"]
    resources: ["pods", "daemonsets", "deployments"]
    verbs: ["create", "delete", "get", "update"]
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: ServiceAccount
metadata:
  name: opsrampagent
  namespace: opsramp-agent
automountServiceAccountToken: true
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: ServiceAccount
metadata:
  name: opsrampagentupdate
  namespace: opsramp-agent
automountServiceAccountToken: true
---
kind: ClusterRoleBinding
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
metadata:
  name: opsrampagentrb
subjects:
  - kind: ServiceAccount
    name: opsrampagent
    namespace: opsramp-agent
roleRef:
  kind: ClusterRole
  name: opsrampagentcr
  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io
---
kind: ClusterRoleBinding
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
metadata:
  name: agentupdaterb
subjects:
  - kind: ServiceAccount
    name: opsrampagentupdate
    namespace: opsramp-agent
roleRef:
  kind: ClusterRole
  name: agent-updater
  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io
---
apiVersion: apps/v1
# Kubernetes Versions after 1.9.0 should use apps/v1
# Kubernetes Versions before 1.8.0 should use extensions/v1beta1 or apps/v1beta1
kind: DaemonSet
metadata:
  name: opsramp-agent-worker
  namespace: opsramp-agent
spec:
  updateStrategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  minReadySeconds: 10
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      name: opsramp-agent-worker
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        name: opsramp-agent-worker
    spec:
      hostNetwork: true
      hostPID: true
      tolerations:
        - key: node-role.kubernetes.io/master
          effect: NoSchedule
      containers:
        - image: opsramp/agent
          imagePullPolicy: Always
          name: opsramp-agent
          terminationMessagePath: /dev/termination-log
          env:
            - name: AGENT_API_KEY
              value: "SZHDyW7vVE5KdDbaxgkXmzCEG5AVyJpv"
            - name: AGENT_API_SECRET
              value: "FgUCMtswA5CTwp3seNa5CaRYneHCMWA4rQx9ey2sPBmJ2WbKRXtHUQFut9W5rvaM"
            - name: INTEGRATION_RES_UUID
              value: "a23c8a8d-7911-4ef4-b93e-cea7121fed9c"
            - name: APP_SERVER
              value: "asura.opsramp.net"
            - name: CLIENT_ID
              value: "client_22843"
            - name: LOG_LEVEL
              value: "warn"
            - name: K8SAGENT
              value: "TRUE"
            - name: DOCKER_EVENTS
              value: "FALSE"
            - name: KUBERNETES_TYPE
              value: "K8S"
            - name: CONTAINER_ENGINE
              value: "ContainerD"
            - name: AUTO_MONITOR
              value: "TRUE"
          resources:
            requests:
              memory: "128Mi"
              cpu: "100m"
            limits:
              memory: "512Mi"
              cpu: "250m"
          securityContext:
            privileged: true
          volumeMounts:
            - name: dockersocket
              mountPath: /run/containerd/containerd.sock
              readOnly: true
            - name: procdir
              mountPath: /host/proc
              readOnly: true
            - name: cgroups
              mountPath: /host/sys/fs/cgroup
              readOnly: true
            - name: mounts
              mountPath: /host/mnt
              readOnly: true
            - name: agent-creds-volume
              mountPath: /opt/opsramp/agent/conf/app.d/creds.yaml
              subPath: creds.yaml
              readOnly: true
            - name: agent-custom-volume
              mountPath: /opt/opsramp/agent/conf/app.d/auto-container-detection.yaml
              subPath: auto-container-detection.yaml
              readOnly: true
      volumes:
        - name: dockersocket
          hostPath:
            path: /run/containerd/containerd.sock
        - name: procdir
          hostPath:
            path: /proc
        - name: cgroups
          hostPath:
            path: /sys/fs/cgroup
        - name: mounts
          hostPath:
            path: /mnt
        - name: agent-creds-volume
          configMap:
            name: agent-creds
        - name: agent-custom-volume
          configMap:
            name: agent-custom
      serviceAccount: opsrampagent
      terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 10
---
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: opsramp-agent-master
  namespace: opsramp-agent
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: opsramp-k8s-agent
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: opsramp-k8s-agent
    spec:
      containers:
        - name: test83-opsramp-k8s-agent
          image: opsramp/agent
          imagePullPolicy: Always
          env:
            - name: AGENT_API_KEY
              value: "SZHDyW7vVE5KdDbaxgkXmzCEG5AVyJpv"
            - name: AGENT_API_SECRET
              value: "FgUCMtswA5CTwp3seNa5CaRYneHCMWA4rQx9ey2sPBmJ2WbKRXtHUQFut9W5rvaM"
            - name: APP_SERVER
              value: "asura.opsramp.net"
            - name: CLIENT_ID
              value: "client_22843"
            - name: LOG_LEVEL
              value: "warn"
            - name: K8SAGENT_MASTER
              value: "TRUE"
            - name: MASTER_UUID
              value: "INTG-4d281b5b-5bbe-47eb-903b-63bcd61809d0"
            - name: INTEGRATION_RES_UUID
              value: "a23c8a8d-7911-4ef4-b93e-cea7121fed9c"
            - name: K8S_EVENTS
              value: "FALSE"
            - name: KUBERNETES_TYPE
              value: "K8S"
            - name: CONTAINER_ENGINE
              value: "ContainerD"
            - name: AUTO_MONITOR
              value: "TRUE"
          resources:
            requests:
              memory: "128Mi"
              cpu: "100m"
            limits:
              memory: "512Mi"
              cpu: "250m"
      serviceAccount: opsrampagent
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: kube-events
  labels:
    name: kube-events
  namespace: opsramp-agent
data:
  eventsConfig.yaml: |
    node:
    - RegisteredNode
    - RemovingNode
    - DeletingNode
    - TerminatingEvictedPod
    - NodeReady
    - NodeNotReady
    - NodeSchedulable
    - NodeNotSchedulable
    - CIDRNotAvailable
    - CIDRAssignmentFailed
    - Starting
    - KubeletSetupFailed
    - FailedMount
    - NodeSelectorMismatching
    - InsufficientFreeCPU
    - InsufficientFreeMemory
    - OutOfDisk
    - HostNetworkNotSupported
    - NilShaper
    - Rebooted
    - NodeHasSufficientDisk
    - NodeOutOfDisk
    - InvalidDiskCapacity
    - FreeDiskSpaceFailed
    pod:
    - Failed
    - InspectFailed
    - ErrImageNeverPull
    - Killing
    - OutOfDisk
    - HostPortConflict
    other:
    - FailedBinding
    - FailedScheduling
    - SuccessfulCreate
    - FailedCreate
    - SuccessfulDelete
    - FailedDelete

apiVersion: v1
kind: Namespace
metadata:
  name: opsramp-agent
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: agent-custom
  labels:
    name: agent-custom
  namespace: opsramp-agent
data:
  auto-container-detection.yaml: |-
    ---
    - name: cassandra
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - cassandra
        port-check:
          - 9042
          - 9160
          - 7000
      mon-type: "jmx"
      misc:
        jmx-port: "7199"
    - name: hbase
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - hbase
        port-check:
          - 60010
      mon-type: "jmx"
      misc:
        jmx-port: "7199"
    - name: activemq
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - activemq
        port-check:
          - 61616
      mon-type: "jmx"
      misc:
        jmx-port: "1099"
    - name: kafka
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - kafka
        port-check:
          - 9092
      mon-type: "jmx"
      misc:
        jmx-port: "5199"
    - name: tomcat
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - tomcat
        port-check:
          - 8080
      mon-type: "jmx"
      misc:
        jmx-port: "7199"
    - name: zookeeper
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - zookeeper
        port-check:
          - 2181
      mon-type: "jmx"
      misc:
        jmx-port: "5199"
    - name: websphere
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - websphere
        port-check:
          - 9043
          - 9060
      mon-type: "jmx"
      misc:
        jmx-port: "7199"
    - name: jboss
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - jboss
          - wildfly
        port-check:
          - 9990
      mon-type: "jmx"
      misc:
        jmx-port: "7199"
    - name: weblogic
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - weblogic
        port-check:
          - 7001
      mon-type: "jmx"
      misc:
        jmx-port: "7199"
    - name: solr
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - solr
        port-check:
          - 8983
      mon-type: "jmx"
      misc:
        jmx-port: "7199"
    - name: elasticsearch
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - elasticsearch
        port-check:
          - 9200
          - 9300
    - name: mysql
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - mysql
        port-check:
          - 3306
    - name: redis
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - redis
        port-check:
          - 6379
      misc:
        socket-timeout: "10"
    - name: k8s-apiserver
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - kube-apiserver
        uri-check:
          - "https://<KUBERNETES_SERVICE_HOST>:443/metrics"
    - name: k8s-controller
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - kube-controller-manager
        uri-check:
          - "https://kube-controller-manager-<KUBERNETES_CONTROLLER_HOST>:10252/metrics"
    - name: k8s-scheduler
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - kube-scheduler
        uri-check:
          - "https://kube-scheduler-<KUBERNETES_CONTROLLER_HOST>:10251/metrics"
    - name: k8s-kube-state
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - kube-state-metrics
        uri-check:
          - "http://<kube-state-metrics-service-ip>:<kube-state-metrics-service-port>/metrics"
    - name: k8s-metrics-server
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - metrics-server
        uri-check:
          - "http://<kube-metrics-server-service-ip>:<kube-metrics-server-service-port>/metrics"
    - name: k8s-coredns
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - coredns
        uri-check:
          - "http://<core-dns-pod-ip>:<core-dns-pod-port>/metrics"
    - name: k8s-kubedns
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - kube-dns
        uri-check:
          - "http://<kube-dns-pod-ip>:<kube-dns-pod-port>/metrics"
    - name: nginx
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - nginx
        port-check:
          - 80
    - name: ceph
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - daemon
      misc:
        cephbinary: "/usr/bin/ceph"
        socketdir: "/var/run/ceph"
    - name: hdfs-namenode
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - namenode
        port-check:
          - 50070
          - 9870
    - name: hdfs-datanode
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - datanode
        port-check:
          - 50075
          - 9864
    - name: memcached
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - memcached
        port-check:
          - 11211
    - name: mongodb
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - mongo
        port-check:
          - 27017
          - 27018
          - 27019
    - name: squid
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - squid
        port-check:
          - 3128
    - name: spark
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - spark
        port-check:
          - 8080
    - name: rabbitmq
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - rabbitmq
        port-check:
          - 15672
          - 5672
      misc:
        queue-names: ""
    - name: lighttpd
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - lighttpd
        port-check:
          - 80
    - name: monit
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - monit
        port-check:
          - 2812
    - name: apache
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - httpd
        port-check:
          - 80
    - name: postgresql
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - postgres
        port-check:
          - 5432
        #  monitoring-configs :
        #    #   The name of the PostgresSQL database to monitor.
        #    #   Note: If omitted, the default system Postgres database is queried.
        #    dbname: $DBNAME
        #    #   ssl type could be any of these := disable , allow, prefer, require, verify-ca, verify-full
        #    ssl: disable
        #    #   The list of relations/tables must be specified here to track per-relation (table) metrics.
        #    #   If enabled, `dbname` should be specified to collect database-specific relations metrics.
        #    #   You can either specify a single relation by its exact name in relation_name or use a regex to track metrics in relation_regex
        #    #   By default all schemas are included. To track relations from specific schemas only,
        #    #   you can specify the `schemas` attribute and provide a list of schemas to use for filtering.
        #    relations:
        #      - relation_name: $TABLE_NAME1
        #        schemas:
        #          - $SCHEMA_NAME1
        #      - relation_name: $TABLE_NAME2
        #        schemas:
        #          - $SCHEMA_NAME1
        #          - $SCHEMA_NAME2
        #      - relation_regex: $TABLE_PATTERN1
        #        schemas:
        #          - $SCHEMA_NAME1
        #          - $SCHEMA_NAME2
    - name: cockroachdb
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - cockroach
        port-check:
          - 26257
          - 8080
    - name: oracle
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - oracle
        port-check:
          - 1521
    - name: haproxy
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - haproxy
        port-check:
          - 9000
    - name: eventstore
      container-checks:
        image-check:
          - eventstore
        port-check:
          - 2113
      misc:
        proto: "https"
